Kirilenko shared his memories of the games with Bryant and Jordan in the NBA
The head of the Russian Basketball Federation (RBF) Andrey Kirilenko shared his memories of his games against the legendary Kobe Bryant and Michael Jordan in the matches of the National Basketball Association (NBA).
I knew that Bryant&#39;s pride should not be hurt by some trash talk, so as not to stimulate his sports anger.
Kobe had a killer instinct, so on the court I tried to talk to him so that he would not perceive the game in an aggressive way.
On the court, I gave him compliments: &quot;Oh!
Kobe, well scored, great pass!
Listening to my enthusiastic responses, he almost forgot that he had to once again pick up the ball and score another 3 - 4 points.
We communicated well with Kobe, &quot;Vechernyaya Moskva quotes Kirilenko as saying.
He also spoke about his first game against Jordan.
&quot;I took care of him.
For the first three minutes of the match, I ran in complete admiration for the fact that next to me was a legend that I had only seen on TV.
While my breath was in my goiter with joy, Michael scored a lot of points.
Soon I moved away from enthusiasm, a couple of times covered his throws ...
In that game, my team won, but Jordan still scored 44 points,” added the head of the RSE.
Kirilenko spent 12 seasons in the NBA.
He was selected 24th overall by the Utah Jazz in the 1999 NBA Draft.
In addition to Utah, for which he spent ten seasons, the Russian striker played for the Minnesota Timberwolves and the Brooklyn Nets.
In total, he played 797 games in which he averaged 11.8 points, 5.5 rebounds, 2.7 assists and 1.8 blocks.
