Singer Polina Gagarina called weight loss products
Russian singer Polina Gagarina named five products that helped her correct her figure and subsequently not gain weight again.
First on the list was water.
The singer prefers to drink pure non-carbonated water before each meal in order to dull the feeling of hunger and eat less.
Also, to maintain harmony, vegetable salad, brown rice and seafood are ideal.
Thanks to them, you can make a balanced diet: vegetables contain fiber, rice contains complex carbohydrates, and seafood is a source of protein, beneficial vitamins and amino acids.
For unloading days, the singer chooses apples.
Thanks to these products, Gagarina was able to get rid of 30 extra pounds.
In addition, the singer switched to fractional nutrition - she eats often and little by little and excluded fatty, sweet and high-calorie foods from the diet.
Gagarina does not eat fried foods, pastries, sausages and other semi-finished meat products, writes kp.ru on July 26.
She also replaced red meat with fish and seafood.
Prefers vegetables (except potatoes), whole grains and lots of greens.
Gagarina is also actively engaged in the gym, yoga and jogging.
Earlier, Russian singer Sergey Lazarev told how he was able to lose weight gained during the period of self-isolation.
